Sentencas: The cathode material Pr2-xLaxNi0.85Cu0.1Al0.05O4+delta (PLNCA, x = 0, 0.2, 0.5 and 1.0) was synthesized by an EDTA-citrate process for use in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of an La-doped Pr2Ni0.85Cu0.1Al0.05O4+δ cathode material for an IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The phase structure and compatibility of the PLNCA with a La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 (LSGM) electrolyte was characterized by X-ray diffraction analysis.
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of an La-doped Pr2Ni0.85Cu0.1Al0.05O4+δ cathode material for an IT-SOFC

Sentencas: A test of thermodynamic stability shows that only PrLaNi0.85Cu0.1Al0.05O4+delta can work for 72 h at 700 degrees C without decomposition.
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of an La-doped Pr2Ni0.85Cu0.1Al0.05O4+δ cathode material for an IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The average thermal expansion coefficient of the PLNCA material matches well with that of the LSGM electrolyte.
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of an La-doped Pr2Ni0.85Cu0.1Al0.05O4+δ cathode material for an IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of the PLNCA material varies in the range of 40-80 S cm(-1) at 400 degrees C.
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of an La-doped Pr2Ni0.85Cu0.1Al0.05O4+δ cathode material for an IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The area specific resistance of the PLNCA cathode on LSGM electrolyte was determined to be 0.029, 0.035, 0.036 and 0.037 Omega cm(2) for x = 0, 0.2, 0.5, 1.0 at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of an La-doped Pr2Ni0.85Cu0.1Al0.05O4+δ cathode material for an IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Moreover, the power density of the electrolyte supported single cell for x = 0, 0.2, 0.5, 1.0 was determined to be 392, 357, 350 and 341 mW cm(-2) at 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of an La-doped Pr2Ni0.85Cu0.1Al0.05O4+δ cathode material for an IT-SOFC

Sentencas: Among PLNCA materials, PrLaNi0.85Cu0.1Al0.05O4+delta shows the best compromise between electrochemical properties and thermodynamic stability and could serve as a potential cathode material for application in IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Preparation and electrochemical properties of an La-doped Pr2Ni0.85Cu0.1Al0.05O4+δ cathode material for an IT-SOFC
